-- PetroChina Says Daqing Oilfield Is on Track to Meet Annual Output Target
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-07T00:47:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-07/petrochina-says-daqing-oilfield-is-on-track-to-meet-annual-output-target.html

          
          
             PetroChina Co.’s Daqing oilfield is
on track to meet its annual output target, the parent company
said in a statement posted on its website today.  
 The field’s annual crude output target is 40 million tons,
it said. Daqing produced 1.6 billion cubic meters of gas and
20.06 million tons of crude oil in the first half, according to
the statement.  
 The company’s Tarim oilfield produced 9.3 billion cubic
meters of gas in the first six months, representing 51 percent
of the annual target.  
